  "texts": [
    "To overcome the challenges of standardized storage and sharing simulation model information, we introduce the concept of a Building Simulation Identity Card (BSIC).",
    "The core idea of BSIC is to develop a standard formal framework for characterizing specialized building simulators.",
    "This encompasses the creation of standardized building simulator ontologies and meta-models, along with standardized interfaces, frameworks, and algorithms for their integration in collaborative simulations.",
    "This would then enable users (i.e., design teams) to make informed choices about the combination of building simulators that they will integrate to answer specific questions about a building when conducting collaborative simulations.",
    "BSIC can be a potential solution for addressing the challenges of collaboration, coordination, cooperation, and communication among the various stakeholders involved in the creation of a DT simulation model."
  ],
